	</div>
	
</div>

<div id="post-1302" class="cf post-1302 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2006/02/vonage-ipo/" title="Vonage IPO" rel="bookmark">Vonage IPO</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Feb</p>
			<p class="post-day">9</p>
			<p class="post-year">2006</p>				
		</div>

		So Vonage, the leading hardware-based consumer VOIP company, is going public. Not a surprise whatsoever &#8212; it was just a question of when Vonage would file. It will be very interesting to see how the IPO does. Vonage has been raising and spending money like a drunken sailor, hell-bent on growing its customer base. It&#8217;s a classic Web 1.0 land-grab play. There is no doubt that Vonage has a real ...
		
	</div>

	<div class="post-footer">
		<a class="post-readmore" href="http://werblog.com/2006/02/vonage-ipo/" title="Vonage IPO">
		read more &rarr;</a>
