	</div>
	
</div>

<div id="post-1301" class="cf post-1301 post type-post status-publish format-standard category-uncategorized">

	<h2>
		<span class="post-format"></span>
		<a href="http://werblog.com/2006/02/backwards-spectrum-policy/" title="Backwards spectrum policy" rel="bookmark">Backwards spectrum policy</a>
		
	</h2>

	
	
	<div class="post-bodycopy cf">
	
		<div class="post-date">		
			<p class="post-month">Feb</p>
			<p class="post-day">7</p>
			<p class="post-year">2006</p>				
		</div>

		President Bush&#8217;s new budget proposal includes a provision authorizing the FCC to impose &#8220;user fees&#8221; on unlicensed wireless. This is a dangerous idea, clearly pushed by incumbent licensed wireless operators to dampen competition from innovative new approaches.
		
	</div>

